Here is an example Next.js component that implements a collapsible FAQ menu with Tailwind CSS:

```jsx
export default function Faq({ faqs }) {
  return (
    <div className="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      {faqs.map(faq => (
        <details key={faq.question} className="mb-4">
          <summary className="font-semibold cursor-pointer list-none">
            {faq.question}  
          </summary>

          <p className="mt-2 text-gray-700">{faq.answer}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

The key points:

- Use the `<details>` and `<summary>` elements to create the collapsible content
- Style with Tailwind utilities for font, margins, etc.
- Map over the `faqs` array prop to render each item
- Use `cursor-pointer` on summary for the click affordance
- Add top margin to the answer text for spacing

You would use it like:

```jsx
<Faq
  faqs={[
    {
      question: "How do I contact support?",
      answer: "Email us at support@example.com" 
    },
    // other FAQ items
  ]}
/>
```

